  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HIAS Sexual and Gender-Based Violence Prevention and Response Initiative</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HIAS will support refugees in eastern Chad by providing: a sustainable advocacy and community-based referral system that identifies and prevents sexual and gender-based violence (SGBV); psychosocial support to male and female survivors; and empowerment for women and girls to achieve increased self-reliance, leadership and decision making abilities.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Objective 1: To prevent SGBV by developing robust community-based protection mechanisms, conducting outreach to and education with wide ranging community stakeholders, and building skills and developing pathways to dignified livelihoods for refugees who are vulnerable to or who are already survivors of SGBV. 

Objective 2: To identify SGBV survivors through a community-based support and referral system and respond to the SGBV identified by engaging and linking a growing network of actors in the health, social service, education and legal sectors.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Refugees, vulnerable victims of torture/sexual and gender based violence</narrative>
  </description>
